ZH: 金属会因为腐蚀而失去光泽。
EN: Metal loses its shine due to corrosion.

ZH: 这座古老的城墙已经被腐蚀了许多年。
EN: This ancient city wall has been corroded for many years.

ZH: 海水中的盐分会加速金属的腐蚀速度。
EN: The salt in seawater accelerates the corrosion rate of metal.

ZH: 学校的铁栏杆已经开始腐蚀了。
EN: The iron railing in the school has started to corrode.

ZH: 空气中的氧气是金属腐蚀的主要原因。
EN: Oxygen in the air is the main cause of metal corrosion.

ZH: 腐蚀会大大降低金属的使用寿命。
EN: Corrosion greatly reduces the lifespan of metal.

ZH: 雨水中的酸性物质会加剧石头的腐蚀。
EN: Acidic substances in rainwater worsen the corrosion of stones.

ZH: 铁锈是铁腐蚀的常见表现。
EN: Rust is a common manifestation of iron corrosion.

ZH: 老化的水管被腐蚀引发了漏水问题。
EN: Corrosion in aging pipes leads to leaking issues.

ZH: 镀金的表面可以有效阻止金属腐蚀。
EN: Gold-plated surfaces can effectively prevent metal corrosion.

ZH: 防护油漆可有效减缓木材腐蚀的速度。
EN: Protective paint can effectively slow down the rate of wood corrosion.

ZH: 因为接触了酸性物质，这台机器已经受到了腐蚀。
EN: This machine has been corroded due to contact with acidic substances.

ZH: 塑料袋中含有的气体会腐蚀铁制品。
EN: Gases in plastic bags can corrode iron products.

ZH: 及时更换车辆的腐蚀零件可以延长其寿命。
EN: Timely replacement of corroded parts in vehicles can extend their lifespan.

ZH: 使用防晒霜可以减少皮肤对紫外线的腐蚀。
EN: Using sunscreen can reduce the corrosion of the skin from ultraviolet rays.

ZH: 酸雨对建筑物的腐蚀速度很快。
EN: Acid rain corrodes buildings quickly.

ZH: 不定期清洁管道可以减缓其腐蚀。
EN: Cleaning pipes irregularly can slow down their corrosion.

ZH: 地下水可能会造成管道的腐蚀。
EN: Groundwater may cause corrosion of pipes.

ZH: 油漆可以有效地阻止金属表面的腐蚀。
EN: Paint can effectively prevent corrosion of metal surfaces.
